com.ti.dvt.engine.scripting

Class ProfileAnalysisExport

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.dvt.engine.scripting.ProfileAnalysisExport

  • public class ProfileAnalysisExport
extends java.lang.Object
    A ProfileAnalysisExport object is created by a call to profileAnalysisSession.exportData(). The exported data is stored in and NxN array and can either be saved to disk as a delimited file, or accessed programatically.

    NOTE: ProfileAnalysisExport needs to be used before changing status of ProfileActivity to false.

    ScriptingEnvironment env = new ScriptingEnvironment();

    DebugServer myDebugServer = (DebugServer) env.getServer("DebugServer.1");
    DebugSession myDebugSession = myDebugServer.openSession("*", "*");

    DVTServer myDVTServer = (DVTServer) env.getServer("DVTServer.1");
    ProfileAnalysisSession myProfSession = myProfServer.openSession(myDebugSession, "FunctionProfile");

    ProfileActivity profileActivity = myDebugSession.profileSetup.getActivity("Profile all Functions for CPU Cycles"); profileActivity.setStatus(true); ...

    //Export profile data
    myProfSession.waitUntilProfilingComplete();
    ProfileAnalysisExport[] myProfExport = myProfSession.exportData();

    ...

    myProfSession.terminate();
    myDVTServer.stop();

    myDebugSession.terminate();
    myDebugServer.stop();

      • readCell

        public java.lang.String readCell(int rowIndex,
                                 int columnIndex)
                          throws ScriptingException
        Read a single cell of exported profile data by specifying a recordID and a columnID. Since this object contains a cached value of the exported profile data, you can programatically access the contents of individual cells using this method.
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - the index of the record you wish to read. This is closely tied to the profile configuration file that was used to collect these result. Record 0 is always the header row and does not contain profile data.
        columnIndex - the index of the column you wish to read.
        Returns:
        The contents of that cell as a string.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • readCell

        public java.lang.String readCell(int rowIndex,
                                 java.lang.String columnName)
                          throws ScriptingException
        Read a single cell of exported profile data by specifying a recordID and a column name. Since this object contains a cached value of the exported profile data, you can programatically access the contents of individual cells using this method.
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - the index of the record you wish to read. This is closely tied to the profile configuration file that was used to collect these result. Record 0 is always the header row and does not contain profile data.
        columnName - the name of the column you wish to read. If you pass in the name of a column that was not exported when this class was created, then this method will raise an error.
        Returns:
        The contents of that cell as a string
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • recordCount

        public int recordCount()
        Get the number of records that were exported. Use this in combination with readCell() to iterate over all of the exported profile data.
        Returns:
        The number of exported records (including 1 header row)

      • save

        public java.lang.String save(java.lang.String fileName)
                      throws ScriptingException
        Save the exported profile data to a delimited text file. The default delimiter is a comma, use ProfileAnalysisExport.setExportDelimiter(String) to change the delimiter.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the name of the file to export profile data to. Relative paths are permitted, use ScripingEnvironment.setCurrentDirectory(String) to change the current working directory.
        Returns:
        The path name of the file data was export to. null, if error/exception occurred.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • setExportDelimiter

        Set the delimiter used to export profile data to a text file. The default is a comma.
